name: Casa Bhonsle Restaurant and Bar

reviews.review_text:
This is very old classic restaurant. You get variety of food options here. They had divided into two sections, top floor serves non veg and bottom one serves veg only. Last time I visited, non veg section was closed. I had tried their veg thali which was good. All the items in the plate tasted really well including the chutney which added a unique flavour. Rajma prepared did not played well with my taste palette. Quantity of the items are fulfilling. They serve you two rotis and rice which will make you full for sure.
Overall a good thali.

Not worth the price and hype. Tried the fish thali there. It's priced at 250 rupees and I was not quite satisfied with the quality of fish and the taste as well. The stars of a thali are the rice, curry and fish and I was not happy with either of them. I am guessing they add soda to the rice which kinda bloats you up after the meal.

Next time, I tried their chicken fried rice and chilli chicken. 250 for chilli chicken and 180 rupees for fried rice would be great to pay if it was extraordinarily good. But the taste here was as good as a local Street side Chinese shop.

So nope from my side.

Only Veg restuarant is open. Non Veg is closed for now. Tried out the Makkan Peda and Famous Punjabi Samosa. Great taste. ðŸ‘Œ

Edit: Tried out some items from their Lunch menu ie Veg Pulao(3/5) too much oily and felt like Fried rice, Gobi Dry, little bit overfried (4/5) and Veg thali(4/5).

### Casa Bhonsle Restaurant and Bar: A Culinary Gem in Goa

Nestled in the heart of Goa, **Casa Bhonsle Restaurant and Bar** boasts an impressive rating of **4.2**, gathered from **2,127 reviews** that speak volumes about its reputation. With popular tags like **thali (134)**, **Goan (129)**, **snacks (61)**, and **local (24)** repeatedly surfacing in customer feedback, itâ€™s evident that this establishment prides itself on offering a delightful range of traditional and local flavors.

### Ambiance & Design

Casa Bhonsle emanates a classic charm that immediately transports guests to a bygone era. The restaurant is thoughtfully divided into two sections: the upper floor dedicated to non-vegetarian offerings, while the lower floor caters exclusively to vegetarians. This design not only enhances the dining experience but also respects the diverse culinary preferences of its patrons.

The dÃ©cor features rustic wooden beams and traditional Goan elements, which are accentuated by soft, ambient lighting that creates an inviting atmosphere. Photos shared by customers highlight the warm and welcoming vibe, making it a perfect place for casual dining with friends or family. Although some reviews note that the non-veg section has been temporarily closed, the ambiance remains lively and bustling.

### Menu & Culinary Experience

At Casa Bhonsle, the menu is a treasure trove for food lovers, offering a variety of dishes that cater to both vegetarians and non-vegetarians. The **Veg Thali** receives particular commendations for its rich flavorsâ€”customers note the inclusion of a chutney that adds a special touch to the meal. However, there are mixed feelings regarding their **Fish Thali**, where one reviewer felt that the quality didn't justify the price, hinting at the crucial balance between value and taste.

Specialties like **Makkan Peda** and **Punjabi Samosa** are praised for their deliciousness, while other items from the lunch menu, such as **Veg Pulao** and **Gobi Dry**, draw varying reviews on taste and preparation. The presentation of the dishes is appealing, inviting diners to indulge their senses from the first glance.

### Customer Experience & Service

Feedback regarding the service at Casa Bhonsle leans toward the positive, with reviewers noting the staffâ€™s efficiency and friendliness. The distinct arrangement of dining spaces may facilitate smoother service, although some customers expressed dissatisfaction when the non-veg section was not in operation. This suggests a need for attention to communicating current offerings to avoid disappointing guests eager for specific dishes. 

### Popularity & Reviews

The lively discussions surrounding Casa Bhonsle on social media and various food blogs indicate its status as a well-loved local destination. While the **thali** options receive accolades for their abundance and taste, the inconsistency in some dishes leads to a diversified customer sentiment; some patrons embrace it wholeheartedly, while others believe the quality could improve.

### Utilizing Visual Content

The restaurant's visual appeal is further illustrated through customer-shared images that showcase not only the inviting ambiance but also the colorful array of dishes served. From the expertly plated **Veg Thali** featuring an assortment of curries and rice to the crispy **Punjabi Samosa**, each image encapsulates the essence of Goa's culinary heritage, enticing potential diners.

In summary, **Casa Bhonsle Restaurant and Bar** emerges as a commendable contender in Goa's vibrant food scene, blending tradition with a warm dining experience. With a little fine-tuning in their menu and clearer communication about their offerings, it holds the potential to elevate its reputation even further. Whether you're in search of a hearty thali or a taste of local snacks, this gem promises an enriching culinary journey.
